{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":325,"text":"What I'm going to show you\nare the astonishing molecular machines"},{"time":5666,"text":"that create the living\nfabric of your body."},{"time":8990,"text":"Now molecules are really, really tiny."},{"time":12797,"text":"And by tiny, I mean really."},{"time":16645,"text":"They're smaller\nthan a wavelength of light,"},{"time":18671,"text":"so we have no way\nto directly observe them."},{"time":21751,"text":"But through science,\nwe do have a fairly good idea"},{"time":24118,"text":"of what's going on\ndown at the molecular scale."},{"time":26799,"text":"So what we can do is actually\ntell you about the molecules,"},{"time":29600,"text":"but we don't really have a direct way\nof showing you the molecules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32861,"text":"One way around this is to draw pictures."},{"time":35135,"text":"And this idea is actually nothing new."},{"time":37699,"text":"Scientists have always created pictures"},{"time":40011,"text":"as part of their thinking\nand discovery process."},{"time":42821,"text":"They draw pictures\nof what they're observing with their eyes,"},{"time":45720,"text":"through technology\nlike telescopes and microscopes,"},{"time":48136,"text":"and also what they're thinking\nabout in their minds."},{"time":50599,"text":"I picked two well-known examples,"},{"time":52226,"text":"because they're very well-known\nfor expressing science through art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56180,"text":"And I start with Galileo,\nwho used the world's first telescope"},{"time":59907,"text":"to look at the Moon."},{"time":61117,"text":"And he transformed\nour understanding of the Moon."},{"time":63448,"text":"The perception in the 17th century"},{"time":65105,"text":"was the Moon was a perfect\nheavenly sphere."},{"time":67575,"text":"But what Galileo saw\nwas a rocky, barren world,"},{"time":70583,"text":"which he expressed\nthrough his watercolor painting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73411,"text":"Another scientist with very big ideas,"},{"time":76334,"text":"the superstar of biology\nis Charles Darwin."},{"time":78882,"text":"And with this famous entry\nin his notebook,"},{"time":80950,"text":"he begins in the top left-hand\ncorner with, \"I think,\""},{"time":83814,"text":"and then sketches out\nthe first tree of life,"},{"time":86545,"text":"which is his perception\nof how all the species,"},{"time":89499,"text":"all living things on Earth are connected\nthrough evolutionary history --"},{"time":93381,"text":"the origin of species\nthrough natural selection"},{"time":95652,"text":"and divergence\nfrom an ancestral population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98515,"text":"Even as a scientist,"},{"time":100388,"text":"I used to go to lectures\nby molecular biologists"},{"time":102925,"text":"and find them completely incomprehensible,"},{"time":105674,"text":"with all the fancy technical\nlanguage and jargon"},{"time":107966,"text":"that they would use\nin describing their work,"},{"time":110114,"text":"until I encountered\nthe artworks of David Goodsell,"},{"time":113189,"text":"who is a molecular biologist\nat the Scripps Institute."},{"time":115954,"text":"And his pictures -- everything's accurate\nand it's all to scale."},{"time":119547,"text":"And his work illuminated for me"},{"time":122000,"text":"what the molecular world\ninside us is like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124815,"text":"So this is a transection through blood."},{"time":126864,"text":"In the top left-hand corner,\nyou've got this yellow-green area."},{"time":129865,"text":"The yellow-green area is the fluid\nof blood, which is mostly water,"},{"time":133105,"text":"but it's also antibodies, sugars,\nhormones, that kind of thing."},{"time":136116,"text":"And the red region is a slice\ninto a red blood cell."},{"time":138628,"text":"And those red molecules are hemoglobin."},{"time":140518,"text":"They are actually red;\nthat's what gives blood its color."},{"time":143237,"text":"And hemoglobin acts as a molecular sponge"},{"time":145228,"text":"to soak up the oxygen in your lungs"},{"time":146929,"text":"and then carry it\nto other parts of the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149066,"text":"I was very much inspired\nby this image many years ago,"},{"time":151622,"text":"and I wondered whether\nwe could use computer graphics"},{"time":154197,"text":"to represent the molecular world."},{"time":155825,"text":"What would it look like?"},{"time":157000,"text":"And that's how I really began."},{"time":158863,"text":"So let's begin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160500,"text":"This is DNA in its classic\ndouble helix form."},{"time":162909,"text":"And it's from X-ray crystallography,\nso it's an accurate model of DNA."},{"time":166289,"text":"If we unwind the double helix\nand unzip the two strands,"},{"time":169284,"text":"you see these things that look like teeth."},{"time":171327,"text":"Those are the letters of genetic code,"},{"time":173168,"text":"the 25,000 genes\nyou've got written in your DNA."},{"time":175461,"text":"This is what they typically talk about --\nthe genetic code --"},{"time":178421,"text":"this is what they're talking about."},{"time":180136,"text":"But I want to talk about\na different aspect of DNA science,"},{"time":182930,"text":"and that is the physical nature of DNA."},{"time":184843,"text":"It's these two strands\nthat run in opposite directions"},{"time":187452,"text":"for reasons I can't go into right now."},{"time":189646,"text":"But they physically run\nin opposite directions,"},{"time":191878,"text":"which creates a number of complications\nfor your living cells,"},{"time":195533,"text":"as you're about to see,"},{"time":196786,"text":"most particularly\nwhen DNA is being copied."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199172,"text":"And so what I'm about to show you"},{"time":201114,"text":"is an accurate representation\nof the actual DNA replication machine"},{"time":205154,"text":"that's occurring right now\ninside your body,"},{"time":207235,"text":"at least 2002 biology."},{"time":209357,"text":"So DNA's entering the production line\nfrom the left-hand side,"},{"time":212734,"text":"and it hits this collection,\nthese miniature biochemical machines,"},{"time":215925,"text":"that are pulling apart the DNA strand\nand making an exact copy."},{"time":219093,"text":"So DNA comes in and hits this blue,\ndoughnut-shaped structure"},{"time":222626,"text":"and it's ripped apart\ninto its two strands."},{"time":225419,"text":"One strand can be copied directly,"},{"time":227067,"text":"and you can see these things\nspooling off to the bottom there."},{"time":230014,"text":"But things aren't so simple\nfor the other strand"},{"time":232298,"text":"because it must be copied backwards."},{"time":234087,"text":"So it's thrown out\nrepeatedly in these loops"},{"time":236221,"text":"and copied one section at a time,\ncreating two new DNA molecules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240289,"text":"Now you have billions of this machine\nright now working away inside you,"},{"time":245596,"text":"copying your DNA with exquisite fidelity."},{"time":248676,"text":"It's an accurate representation,"},{"time":250234,"text":"and it's pretty much at the correct speed\nfor what is occurring inside you."},{"time":253787,"text":"I've left out error correction\nand a bunch of other things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256628,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258411,"text":"This was work from a number of years ago--"},{"time":260556,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261749,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":263145,"text":"This is work from a number of years ago,"},{"time":265098,"text":"but what I'll show you next\nis updated science,"},{"time":267389,"text":"it's updated technology."},{"time":268575,"text":"So again, we begin with DNA."},{"time":269959,"text":"And it's jiggling and wiggling there"},{"time":271701,"text":"because of the surrounding\nsoup of molecules,"},{"time":273906,"text":"which I've stripped away\nso you can see something."},{"time":276313,"text":"DNA is about two nanometers across,\nwhich is really quite tiny."},{"time":279312,"text":"But in each one of your cells,"},{"time":280770,"text":"each strand of DNA is about\n30 to 40 million nanometers long."},{"time":284414,"text":"So to keep the DNA organized\nand regulate access to the genetic code,"},{"time":288254,"text":"it's wrapped around these\npurple proteins --"},{"time":290361,"text":"or I've labeled them purple here."},{"time":291967,"text":"It's packaged up and bundled up."},{"time":293575,"text":"All this field of view\nis a single strand of DNA."},{"time":296511,"text":"This huge package of DNA\nis called a chromosome."},{"time":299617,"text":"And we'll come back\nto chromosomes in a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302415,"text":"We're pulling out, we're zooming out,"},{"time":304505,"text":"out through a nuclear pore,"},{"time":306000,"text":"which is the gateway to this compartment\nthat holds all the DNA,"},{"time":309684,"text":"called the nucleus."},{"time":311657,"text":"All of this field of view\nis about a semester's worth of biology,"},{"time":315912,"text":"and I've got seven minutes,"},{"time":317301,"text":"So we're not going to be\nable to do that today?"},{"time":320013,"text":"No, I'm being told, \"No.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":322416,"text":"This is the way a living cell\nlooks down a light microscope."},{"time":325805,"text":"And it's been filmed under time-lapse,\nwhich is why you can see it moving."},{"time":329327,"text":"The nuclear envelope breaks down."},{"time":330932,"text":"These sausage-shaped things\nare the chromosomes,"},{"time":333201,"text":"and we'll focus on them."},{"time":334406,"text":"They go through this very striking motion\nthat is focused on these little red spots."},{"time":339068,"text":"When the cell feels it's ready to go,\nit rips apart the chromosome."},{"time":343327,"text":"One set of DNA goes to one side,"},{"time":345392,"text":"the other side gets\nthe other set of DNA --"},{"time":347439,"text":"identical copies of DNA."},{"time":349300,"text":"And then the cell splits down the middle."},{"time":351284,"text":"And again, you have billions of cells\nundergoing this process"},{"time":354167,"text":"right now inside of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356342,"text":"Now we're going to rewind\nand just focus on the chromosomes,"},{"time":359222,"text":"and look at its structure and describe it."},{"time":361988,"text":"So again, here we are\nat that equator moment."},{"time":365394,"text":"The chromosomes line up."},{"time":366618,"text":"And if we isolate just one chromosome,"},{"time":368469,"text":"we're going to pull it out\nand have a look at its structure."},{"time":371310,"text":"So this is one of the biggest\nmolecular structures that you have,"},{"time":374396,"text":"at least as far as we've discovered\nso far inside of us."},{"time":378026,"text":"So this is a single chromosome."},{"time":380026,"text":"And you have two strands of DNA\nin each chromosome."},{"time":382651,"text":"One is bundled up into one sausage."},{"time":384396,"text":"The other strand is bundled up\ninto the other sausage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387153,"text":"These things that look like whiskers\nthat are sticking out from either side"},{"time":390739,"text":"are the dynamic scaffolding of the cell."},{"time":392669,"text":"They're called microtubules,\nthat name's not important."},{"time":395604,"text":"But we're going to focus on\nthe region labeled red here --"},{"time":398359,"text":"and it's the interface between\nthe dynamic scaffolding"},{"time":400920,"text":"and the chromosomes."},{"time":402111,"text":"It is obviously central\nto the movement of the chromosomes."},{"time":405240,"text":"We have no idea, really,\nas to how it's achieving that movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408836,"text":"We've been studying this thing\nthey call the kinetochore"},{"time":411507,"text":"for over a hundred years\nwith intense study,"},{"time":413603,"text":"and we're still just beginning\nto discover what it's about."},{"time":416453,"text":"It is made up of about\n200 different types of proteins,"},{"time":419231,"text":"thousands of proteins in total."},{"time":421730,"text":"It is a signal broadcasting system."},{"time":424574,"text":"It broadcasts through chemical signals,"},{"time":426762,"text":"telling the rest of the cell\nwhen it's ready,"},{"time":429530,"text":"when it feels that everything\nis aligned and ready to go"},{"time":432385,"text":"for the separation of the chromosomes."},{"time":434387,"text":"It is able to couple onto the growing\nand shrinking microtubules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437743,"text":"It's involved with the growing\nof the microtubules,"},{"time":440966,"text":"and it's able to transiently\ncouple onto them."},{"time":444099,"text":"It's also an attention-sensing system."},{"time":445943,"text":"It's able to feel when the cell is ready,"},{"time":447943,"text":"when the chromosome\nis correctly positioned."},{"time":450201,"text":"It's turning green here because it feels\nthat everything is just right."},{"time":454038,"text":"And you'll see,\nthere's this one little last bit"},{"time":456320,"text":"that's still remaining red."},{"time":457777,"text":"And it's walked away\ndown the microtubules."},{"time":461889,"text":"That is the signal broadcasting system\nsending out the stop signal."},{"time":465092,"text":"And it's walked away --\nI mean, it's that mechanical."},{"time":467812,"text":"It's molecular clockwork."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469404,"text":"This is how you work\nat the molecular scale."},{"time":472609,"text":"So with a little bit\nof molecular eye candy,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":474897,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":476119,"text":"we've got kinesins, the orange ones."},{"time":478093,"text":"They're little molecular courier\nmolecules walking one way."},{"time":480890,"text":"And here are the dynein,\nthey're carrying that broadcasting system."},{"time":484060,"text":"And they've got their long legs"},{"time":485628,"text":"so they can step around\nobstacles and so on."},{"time":487718,"text":"So again, this is all derived\naccurately from the science."},{"time":490769,"text":"The problem is we can't show it\nto you any other way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493343,"text":"Exploring at the frontier of science,\nat the frontier of human understanding,"},{"time":498201,"text":"is mind-blowing."},{"time":500714,"text":"Discovering this stuff"},{"time":501916,"text":"is certainly a pleasurable\nincentive to work in science."},{"time":505960,"text":"But most medical researchers --"},{"time":508641,"text":"discovering the stuff is simply steps\nalong the path to the big goals,"},{"time":512878,"text":"which are to eradicate disease,\nto eliminate the suffering"},{"time":517323,"text":"and the misery that disease causes"},{"time":519422,"text":"and to lift people out of poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521126,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522422,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}